SIMPLE: waiter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waiter
<hw>Wait"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, waits; an attendant; a servant in attendance, esp. at
table.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>waiters</qex> stand in ranks; the yeomen cry,⟦br⟧
⟦ldquo⟧Make room,⟦rdquo⟧ as if a duke were passing by.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vessel or tray on which something is carried, as
dishes, etc.; a salver.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Coast waiter</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Coast</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waiting</ent>⟦br⟧
